sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    participant User as User / Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Webhook as Mutating/Validating Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS (serving-cert)
    participant RCCtrl as RayCluster Controller
    participant AuthCtrl as Authentication Controller
    participant mTLSCtrl as mTLS Controller
    participant NPCtrl as NetworkPolicy Controller
    participant Gateway as Platform Gateway<br/>(data-science-gateway)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant KRBP as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>(head pod sidecar)<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant RayDash as Ray Dashboard<br/>(head pod)<br/>8265/TCP HTTP

    rect rgb(230, 245, 255)
        Note over User,RayDash: Flow 1: RayCluster Creation with Authentication (RHOAI)
        User->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply RayCluster<br/>Bearer Token / TLS 1.2+
        K8sAPI->>Webhook: Admission request<br/>HTTPS/9443 (API server client cert)
        Note right of Webhook: Defaults odh.ray.io/secure-trusted-network=true<br/>Forces enableIngress=false
        Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Mutated + validated response

        K8sAPI-->>RCCtrl: Watch event: RayCluster created
        RCCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create head Pod, worker Pods, Services<br/>ServiceAccount Token / TLS 1.2+

        K8sAPI-->>AuthCtrl: Watch event: RayCluster with auth annotation
        AuthCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create HTTPRoute (platform ns),<br/>ReferenceGrant, ConfigMap, ServiceAccount<br/>ServiceAccount Token / TLS 1.2+
        Note right of AuthCtrl: Injects kube-rbac-proxy sidecar<br/>into head pod spec

        K8sAPI-->>mTLSCtrl: Watch event: RayCluster
        mTLSCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create SelfSigned Issuer, CA Certificate,<br/>Head/Worker Certificates (cert-manager)<br/>ServiceAccount Token / TLS 1.2+

        K8sAPI-->>NPCtrl: Watch event: RayCluster
        NPCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create NetworkPolicies<br/>ServiceAccount Token / TLS 1.2+
    end

    rect rgb(255, 248, 225)
        Note over User,RayDash: Flow 1 (cont): User Accesses Ray Dashboard
        User->>Gateway: GET /ray-dashboard<br/>HTTPS/443, OIDC/OAuth cookie
        Gateway->>KRBP: Forward request<br/>HTTPS/8443 (TLS, self-signed)
        KRBP->>K8sAPI: TokenReview + SubjectAccessReview<br/>Validates user has 'get' on services/{cluster}-head-svc
        K8sAPI-->>KRBP: Auth result
        KRBP->>RayDash: Forward to dashboard<br/>HTTP/8265 (localhost)
        RayDash-->>KRBP: Dashboard response
        KRBP-->>Gateway: Response
        Gateway-->>User: Dashboard page
    end

    rect rgb(232, 245, 233)
        Note over User,RayDash: Flow 2: RayJob Submission (K8sJobMode)
        User->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply RayJob<br/>Bearer Token / TLS 1.2+
        K8sAPI-->>RCCtrl: RayJob Controller creates RayCluster (if needed)
        RCCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create K8s Job (submitter pod)<br/>ServiceAccount Token
        Note right of RCCtrl: Submitter Job pod runs ray job submit
        RCCtrl->>RayDash: Submit job via REST API<br/>HTTP/8265 (no auth, cluster-internal)
        loop Status polling
            RCCtrl->>RayDash: GET /api/jobs/{id}<br/>HTTP/8265
            RayDash-->>RCCtrl: Job status
        end
    end

    rect rgb(252, 228, 236)
        Note over User,RayDash: Flow 3: RayService Zero-Downtime Upgrade
        User->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply RayService (updated)<br/>Bearer Token / TLS 1.2+
        Note over RCCtrl: RayService Controller
        RCCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create pending RayCluster<br/>ServiceAccount Token
        RCCtrl->>RayDash: PUT serve config to pending cluster<br/>HTTP/8265
        RCCtrl->>RayDash: Health check via HTTP Proxy<br/>HTTP/8000
        RayDash-->>RCCtrl: Healthy
        RCCtrl->>K8sAPI: Update serve-svc selector → pending cluster
        RCCtrl->>K8sAPI: Delete old active RayCluster
    end
